Digital Clock Web App
Overview:
This is a simple digital clock built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It displays the current time in the HH:MM:SS format, updating dynamically every second. The clock features a modern design with a gradient background and responsive layout, making it visually appealing and easy to use on any device.

Key Features:
Real-time time updates.
Minimalist and responsive design.
Lightweight and fast performance.
Technologies Used:
HTML: Provides the structure.
CSS: Creates the visual styling.
JavaScript: Handles real-time updates.

Use Cases:
Embed as a widget on a website.
Learn basic web development.
Showcase dynamic JavaScript functionality.
Future Enhancements:
Support for different time zones.
Toggle between 12-hour and 24-hour formats.
Display the current date.
This project is perfect for beginners and can be hosted easily using GitHub Pages, Netlify, or other platforms.
